title: Ya Kun Kaya Toast
name: Leslie Seah
text:
UPDATE: 6 months later.  There are now more staff. 3 people now. The wait time is now acceptable.  Thank you.  Cleanliness is still an issue though. I hear at 4pm. Popular hour for an afternoon coffee break. No one to clean the tables. Presently, there’s a tie-up with Samsung. Tables are covered a silvery Samsung Galaxy AI advertisement. Dirt and stains stick to this.  I tried cleaning with tissue and alcoholic spray.  Doesn’t work.

I’m a regular Ya Kun customer at various outlets depending on where my day takes me.  Food & beverages at this outlet are up to par. However, this outlet is poorly managed.  Often there’re only 2 people running this outlet. It’s not the fault of staff on site. An outlet like this REQUIRES more than 2. It takes forever to place an order because the person taking orders also has to brew the coffee/tea. The second guy makes the food/toast.  Nobody to clean the tables. I often leave tables much cleaner than I find it. I pay. I clean. I drink. I clear.
POOR MANAGEMENT. This isn’t a food court or hawker center or Kopitiam. Legally, I’m not obligated to clear my cups.  Taking customers for granted.

text:
This outlet in Funan has switched to only disposable cups/ utensils, no matter dining in or takeout. This is environmental unfriendly.

When I suggested to the man in black collared tee that my dine-in order doesn't need a cover (which he used to communicate an order with marker), it was met with silence.

I'm sure there are valid reasons why disposables are used. But at least rely on your own receipt to prepare the drinks for dine-in, no need extra cup covers (wastage).

text:
Ich bin leider mehr als enttäuscht von diesem Restaurant. Es stand eine lange Schlange vor dem Restaurant weshalb wir uns gedacht haben, dort zu frühstücken. Mitarbeitende sind recht freundlich aber von dem Essen bin ich enttäuscht. Erstmal gab es zu dem Zeitpunkt keine Eier mehr für das frühstücksset und dann habe ich nur einen toast und einen Eis Kaffee genommen. Der toast war allerdings keine ganze Scheibe sondern 2 endstücke, die trocken, zerfallen und halb so groß waren wie die normalen Scheiben. Deshalb auch dem Preis nixht angemessen. Der Eiskaffee war auch nicht kalt, da ein paar Eiswürfel schwer einen ganzen becher warmen Kaffee kühlen können.
Noch einmal werde ich hier nicht essen!
textTranslated:
Unfortunately, I am more than disappointed with this restaurant. There was a long line in front of the restaurant so we thought we would have breakfast there. Employees are quite friendly but I'm disappointed with the food. First of all, there were no more eggs for the breakfast set at that point and then I just took toast and an iced coffee. However, the toast wasn't a whole slice but rather 2 end pieces that were dry, falling apart and half the size of the normal slices. Therefore not appropriate for the price. The iced coffee wasn't cold either, as a few ice cubes can hardly cool an entire cup of warm coffee.
I won't eat here again!

ร้านนี้มีหลายสาขาส่วนมากจะอยู่ใน Shopping Mall หรือห้างสรรพสินค้าในสิงคโปร์
textTranslated:
It's a popular shop for locals. Singaporeans will queue up very long in the morning to buy breakfast. This shop's most popular set includes flat toast with butter or cream that has a unique flavor. Salty and sweet, just the right balance. This shop has a very long history and is well known in the Singaporean community. If anyone comes to visit, try stopping by for breakfast or afternoon coffee and snacks at Singaporeans call it "Kopi". The taste of the iced coffee is not sweet because of the condensed milk like in our country in Thailand, but it is sweet enough. Not a lot of ice is added, giving a strong flavor to the coffee.

This shop has many branches, mostly in Shopping Malls or department stores in Singapore.
